"Yes, sir. They should already be on their way, we gave them time to pack food from the mess hall." 05:00, Exodus Company gathered at the vehicle bay. Lieutenant Xiao stood on a box and began speaking.
"We will head to the I-131 frontline base 50 miles outside Ianlos City. We will support the ongoing siege operation, then attack Ianlos City to clear out the rebels there. We will use this as a base to advance into the mountains." Lieutenant Xiao explained. "Take your squad and prepare to depart."
The company dispersed, with each platoon boarding their tanks under the lead of their respective platoon leaders. Kolen climbed aboard one of the lead tanks in the convoy and sat beside Nimchy, Crees, and two new recruits. Kolen remembered they had just arrived a few days ago but knew little about them. He sat at the edge of the tank, his legs dangling, adjusting his backpack and radio equipment, and connecting it to his headphones and throat microphone.
"Hey, Kolen, did Harris still have Snowball?" Nimchy asked after they were settled.
"You mean the chicken he stole?" Kolen recalled the morning when they stole chickens from the farm. "Yes, I'm sure of it."
Kolen looked at another tank and saw Harris and his team. He vaguely saw a small chicken peering around behind Harris's backpack.
"Right, he still has the chicken," Kolen replied. At that moment, the hatch of the turret opened with a bang, and the commander appeared before them.
"All tanks are underway," the commander said calmly and clearly through his helmet microphone. The armored platoon's tanks and Stryker armored vehicles roared to life and began moving forward. Kolen's Krona tank released its brakes and moved forward, joining the formation. The tanks took up a wedge formation as they crossed the Iteania plain. Winter snowstorm had frozen the wetlands and forests, but the mud was still present.
About an hour later, a new recruit (Kolen remembered his name was Osen) asked, "Lieutenant, have you been on the front line since the start?"
"Yes, since the Stormcast action began," Kolen replied. "We thought the battle would be over in a few weeks, but... we underestimated them."
"We underestimated them by more than just a little," Nimchy joined in the conversation. "Their weapons and troop numbers exceeded our expectations. They shot down the UFS Revenant in the first two weeks and the Erebus last month. Damn, we should have seen it coming on the road."
"Alright, I'll bravely fight for the federation," Osen said resolutely. "I won't be scared by those terrorists."
"You say that now, but from what I've seen, most new recruits like you are too afraid to even hear a gunshot," Crees said.
"We'll see about that," Kolen said with a smile. Osen didn't say anything else.
"Exodus Deputy Commander! Exodus Commander!" Kolen's radio equipment emitted a call. "We've detected a thermal signal 20 degrees, 350 yards ahead on the right."
Kolen climbed aboard the tank and put on his optical goggles. Switching to thermal imaging mode, he saw the distant heat signatures.
"Yes, I see them," Kolen said into his throat microphone.
"Are they enemies?" another new recruit named Natalie asked.
"Can't tell yet," Kolen replied, turning on the microphone. "Exodus Platoon, do not engage unless attacked. Wait until they come out."
As they got closer, the faint heat signatures became clearer outlines. One of them ran to a spot, picked something up, and ran back to the ridge. Then, they crouched down and took their positions for firing.
"We're encountering enemies!" Lieutenant Xiao shouted over the radio as orange tracers lit up the hilltop. Bullets pinged off the sides of the tanks, and the突击队员们纷纷跳下坦克，躲在坦克后面。一枚反坦克导弹呼啸着飞了过来，猛地撞向坦克编队后方的地面，爆炸碎片击中了其中一辆坦克。另一枚导弹击中了一辆史赛克装甲车（APS-Cerberus）的侧面并爆炸。弹药殉爆后，装甲车内的机组人员纷纷爬了出来，寻找掩护。
"Iron 1-2 and 1-3, 25 degrees to the right, 300 yards. Fire!" the tank platoon leader shouted over the radio. The main guns of Iron 1-2 and 1-3 opened fire, sending shells whizzing towards the hilltop, explosions sending dirt and rocks flying into the air.
"Send out sentry robots!" Knox, who was using a telescope to observe the hilltop, called out. The rear hatch of a M2 Bradley (Hellhound) opened, and a soldier without a weapon walked out, wearing special earphones. He barked orders into a square microphone, and two sentry robots emerged in response. Their long metal arms and legs swung forward, propelling them to run quickly. The robots were armed but had their weapons slung across their backs.
"Kill or capture?" Crees asked as he observed.
"Looks like we're capturing live prisoners," Kolen guessed, watching as the two sentry robots disappeared into the ash and smoke. Shouts and gunfire echoed from the hilltop but soon quieted down. After a while, the two sentry robots returned, dragging a person between them. The prisoner’s boots left marks in the mud and snow. Once they reached a safe area, the robots dropped the captive, who crashed to the ground in the mud and snow, groaning in pain.
He struggled to stand up, and Lieutenant Xiao walked over. Lieutenant Xiao turned to one of the sentries.
"Three deaths, sir," the sentry robot replied. "The rest have escaped on foot."
Lieutenant Xiao nodded and turned to Kolen and Crees, who were standing nearby. "Can you two take this person away?"
